Diagnosis : Scorpions of medium to large size (
Figs. 4–5
), ranging from 60 to 72 mm in males and 66 to 75 mm in females; General coloration yellow to yellowish green; ocular tubercle located on anterior half of prosoma with following index: 0.65 ± 0.025 ; dentate margins of fixed and movable fingers of pedipalps with 12–13 rows of oblique denticles; longer movable finger relative to the manus length (MFL/ML 1.88–2.66 ); ventrosubmedian carinae of metasomal segments II–III with three to five pairs of distinct denticles; anterior ventral margin of metasomal segment IV with transverse row of eight or more enlarged granules; Metasomal segment IV L/W 1.80 ± 0.128 ; ventrolateral carinae of metasomal segment V with three strong lobate denticles; Lateral anal arch armed with two strong and one minor lobe; posterior ventral margin of metasomal segment V with six reduced lobes; smaller and narrower telson (TlL/W 2.06 ± 0.142 ; TlL/H 2.20 ± 0.151 ).
